definition: to leave blank space in a document/to leave some time free
to leave (a message etc)/to retain/to stay/to remain/to keep/to preserve

sentences.english: The ribbon should wrap around the spine with excess on either side.
sentences.chinese: 带子要绕在书脊上，两边都要留空。

sentences.english: Reserve space in object names for a class-of-service qualifier.
sentences.chinese: 在对象名称中为分类服务限定符保留空间。

sentences.english: The other text fields are optional and can be left blank.
sentences.chinese: 其他文本字段是可选的，可以留空。

sentences.english: Keep empty to use the default UOM.
sentences.chinese: 留空以使用默认计量单位。

sentences.english: The Alias name should be left blank in most cases.
sentences.chinese: 大部分情况下别名是留空的。

sentences.english: So we can now turn our nanofluidic devices on and off.
sentences.chinese: 然后我们就能控制纳留空装置的开关。

sentences.english: As in Adventure 2, leave spaces after each identified belief and each category of beliefs.
sentences.chinese: 依照冒险2，在每个分类信念后面留空。

sentences.english: Did I not instruct that Box Five was to be kept empty?
sentences.chinese: 难道我没下过指令，让你们把第五号包厢给我留空吗？

sentences.english: Users of U. S. English keyboards should generally leave this entry blank.
sentences.chinese: 美国英语键盘用户通常应该将此栏留空。
